message: /* Request to add two famous modern South Indian Brahmins to the Brahmin page */ new section

The Bhakti movement section glorifies the community -  but it is mainly the South Indian Brahmins who were responsible for social reforms, South Indian Brahmins are different from North Indian Brahmins. So I credited the glorification to South Indian Brahmins, one Bengali and one Gujarati Brahmin. exception is Ramananda who is a North Indian Brahmin. Manusmriti uses the word Brahmana so used the word Brahmanas to which the modern Brahmin community belongs to.
